	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">A funny thing about shard/fragment camping is that I spent a lot of time there soloing and using my druid (quadding/rotting) to attempt to make things a little more fun.. but none of those times did I obtain a shard on my own.  I looted 2 during these times from other groups, 1 from a group while I was prepping for another cleric's run at Ragefire, and I don't recall how I got the last one.  I'm thinking I had it early and forgot about it <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="Wink"><br />
<br />
I brought a bunch of friends there once, created trains like no man has seen and took us through endless battles of adds and so many chromadrac debuffs I thought we'd go mad.. and didn't see a shard.<br />
<br />
My advice would be to park your cleric there or play there when other groups are there.. (unless they are hunting for shards, to<img src="images/smilies/alien.gif" border="0" alt="Alien"> and hope you get lucky.  I found no rhyme or reason for the drops... I know two of mine came from a wyvern/wurm.. and i know the third was from a guardian wurm near VP, so it's completely random as everyone has attested to.<br />
<br />
Good luck!</font></p>
	
