	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 01-06-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">08:35 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Honest, I've seen the most fragments drop hunting in the southeast corner of the zone.  I don't know why.  Maybe it's just a statistical anomaly.  But every time I've hunted there, whether for fragments or just soloing my druid for exp, I've gotten at least one fragment per few hours.  When I was there for Binkin's fragments, we got all four on a single evening.  There's a safe area at the southeast corner of the moon temple (the one you can see to your left when you stand at the tunnel to OT), just settle in there and pull as fast as your group can handle.  You can also fear kite once you learn the pathing if you or someone else can snare.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

Binkin<br />
61 Gnomish High Priest<br />
Battle Cleric of Mischief and Bright Pink Bouncy Ball of DOOM!<br />
Xev
</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
