	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 01-15-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">06:20 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Collected all 4 fragments in under 4 hours.<br />
<br />
The trick was take a group of 65's from my guild, send the druid out to pull trains into the BW zoneline and slaughter them on the spot, I CH'ed the MT, the Enchanter was there for CC and the rest of the guys were DPS.<br />
<br />
We cleared the zone twice I think barring the one mob we avoided, the Chromodracs because of the damn dispelling.<br />
<br />
I think the honestly think the key is quantity, the people I've talked to who said it took days were generally duoing with a partner and the kill rate was quite low. <br />
<br />
Kill em hard and fast and the fragments drop at a reasonable pace.<br />
<br />
<br />
Fickfighs - Level 64 Servant of Brell.</font></p>
	
